ABOUT:
Leaf Scald is a fungal disease caused by Microdochium oryzae. It leads to elongated water-soaked lesions that dry and turn pale.

SYMPTOMS:
Water-soaked elongated lesions
Bleached or white patches on leaves
Drying of leaf tips
Irregular leaf blight appearance

PREVENTION:
Ensure proper drainage and irrigation
Avoid overcrowding of plants
Apply seed treatment fungicides
Use resistant varieties when available
